 <item> <title>Important Information on the Derecognition of ACICS</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/acics</link>
 <description>On December 12, 2016, the Secretary upheld the decision of the Senior Department Official (SDO) to cease recognition of the Accrediting Council for Independent Colleges and Schools (ACICS) as an agency that can provide schools with a seal of approval for educational quality, which in turn makes schools eligible to participate in federal student aid programs.</description>
